qas.question: How many theater companies does Seattle have in residence?
What Seattle theater was built in 1926?
To what type of theater are the two dozen live venues in Seattle associated?
To what type of theater is Seattle second to New York?
How many equity theaters does Seattle have?

context: The <a1_0>5th Avenue Theatre<a1_0/>, built in 1926, stages Broadway-style musical shows featuring both local talent and international stars. Seattle has "<a0_0>around 100<a0_0/>" theatrical production companies and over two dozen live theatre venues, many of them associated with <a2_0>fringe theatre<a2_0/>; Seattle is probably second only to New York for number of <a3_0>equity theaters<a3_0/> (<a4_0>28<a4_0/> Seattle theater companies have some sort of Actors' Equity contract). In addition, the 900-seat Romanesque Revival Town Hall on First Hill hosts numerous cultural events, especially lectures and recitals.
